<p>
<seg id=1> International supervisory personnel in Kosovo still see hope of restoring cease-fire, in spite of the battle in several days running between Salvia security army and Albania separatists. </seg>
<seg id=2> A spokesman of supervisory personnel expressed in Pristina on Monday that the present situation in Kosovo of Yugoslavia is calm. </seg>
<seg id=3> The battle of last week killed at least 12 persons. </seg>
<seg id=4> Chairman of European Security and Co-operation Organization, Polish Gelmeike condemned this violent conflict caused by both parties of the battle. </seg>
</p>
